results.name: Replace each prime p in prime-factorization of n with p-th Fibonacci number.
comment: If, for p = prime, p^(m_{n,p}) is highest power of p dividing n, m = nonnegative integer, then a(n) is product over all primes of F(p)^(m_{n,p}), where F(p) = p-th Fibonacci number (A000045).
link: Danny Rorabaugh, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..4000
formula: Totally multiplicative with a(p) = F(p). - _Franklin T. Adams-Watters_, Jun 05 2006
mathematica: b[t_]:=Fibonacci[First[t]]^Last[t] a[n_]:=Apply[Times, Map[b, FactorInteger[n]]] (* Esa Peuha, Oct 26 2005 *)
program: (Sage) [1]+[prod([fibonacci(x[0])^x[1] for x in factor(n)]) for n in range(2,53)] # _Danny Rorabaugh_, Apr 03 2015
